  "text": "Further, continuous functions or square-integrable functions on finite domains can be approximated with arbitrarily small error by a feed-forward network with one or two hidden layers [CITATION_1] ]. Similarly, we use a fully-connected neural network to represent this function, as shown in Fig.4 .",
